text:
North (Hudson) River, showing (left) pier 86, off Twelfth Ave., at the foot of West 46th Street.

August 31, 1926.

P. L. Sperr.
title: North (Hudson) River - Pier 86.

text:
Twelfth Avenue, west side, north from West 46th Street. The buildings that formerly stood at 47th Street have been demolished. In the basin at the left is to be constructed a new 1000 foot pier. This will be No. 88 North River and will be used by the French Line. This site is enclosed in View 2.

April 10, 1931
July 23, 1932

P. L. Sperr
